FBIS4-40297 "drsov116_a_94042" FBIS-SOV-94-116 Daily Report 16 Jun 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Kozyrev Cited on Closer Cooperation With CIS Kozyrev Cited on Closer Cooperation With CIS LD1606094994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0922 GMT 16 Jun 94 LD1606094994 Moscow ITAR-TASS English BFN [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondents Yuriy Kozlov and Boris Krivoshey] [Text] Moscow June 16 TASS -- Russia would like to encourage closer cooperation and further integration between the country- members of the Commonwealth of Independent States. "We are ready for as much integration as our partners are", announced Russian Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev on Thursday. Speaking at a foreign policy council meeting devoted to the further integration of the CIS countries and to Russian interests, Kozyrev noted the appearance of a lot of far-reaching ideas which "show the urge for closer integration". "At the same time, we would like to avoid a situation in which the proposal and discussion of such promising ideas hinders us in resolving concrete pressing problems, or distracts our attention from them", Kozyrev said.
